C%20with%20a%20median%20drop%20of%201%25%2C%20but%20when%20an%20incumbent%20party%20wins%20the%20election%20in%20November%2C%20the%20early%20part%20of%20the%20year%20sees%20an%20average%20gain%20rather%20than%20a%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20an%20incumbent%20Democrat%20has%20gone%20on%20to%20win%2C%20the%20DJIA%20has%20risen%20a%20median%20of%202.6%25%20in%20the%20first%20two%20months%20of%20the%20year%20versus%20a%206.2%25%20decline%20when%20an%20incumbent%20Democrat%20has%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20Clissold%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClissold%20acknowledges%20that%20two%20months%20of%20stock%20market%20performance%20is%20by%20no%20means%20a%20determining%20factor%20of%20a%20Presidential%20election%2C%20but%20it's%20interesting%20nonetheless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20two-month%20window%20eight%20months%20before%20the%20election%20is%20hardly%20the%20most%20robust%20indicator%2C%20especially%20considering%20how%20many%20factors%20beyond%20the%20stock%20market%20go%20into%20voters'%20decision-making%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Clissold%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20if%20the%20stock%20market%20is%20rising%20ahead%20of%20the%20November%20election%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20that%20means%20the%20economy%20is%20doing%20well%20and%20consumer%20confidence%20is%20improving%2C%20so%20that%20backdrop%20could%20ultimately%20provide%20a%20tailwind%20to%20Biden's%20re-election%20chances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%2030%2C000-foot%20perspective%2C%20a%20better%20economic%20backdrop%20would%20help%20Biden's%20chances%2C%26quot%3B%20Clissold%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-signal-presidential-reelection-joe-biden-incumbent-donald-trump-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709396309000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e21a19ce7f1785b2e57ab3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22h