20%2415%2C000%20Al%20Jazeera%20Documentary%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Leo%20Barraclough%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fcphdox-once-upon-a-time-in-a-forest-autlook-1235928268%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fcphdox-once-upon-a-time-in-a-forest-autlook-1235928268%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fcphdox-once-upon-a-time-in-a-forest-autlook-1235928268%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Ameen%20Sayani%20Helped%20Unite%20the%20Soul%20of%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F21200240%2FAmeen-Sayani.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20after%20the%20sad%20death%20of%20the%20one%20and%20only%20Ameen%20Sayani%2C%20I%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20photo%20with%20him%2C%20taken%20by%20his%20son%20at%20the%20National%20Centre%20for%20the%20Performing%20Arts%20(NCPA)%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20in%20which%20%E2%80%98August%202019%E2%80%99%20was%20scrawled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20gone%20there%20to%20deliver%20the%20Jamshed%20Bhaba%20Memorial%20Talk%20on%20Indian%20culture.%20I%20was%20his%20great%20admirer%20and%20came%20to%20know%20him%20from%20the%20time%20I%20headed%20All%20India%20Radio%20and%20Doordarshan%20as%20the%20chief%20executive%20officer%20(CEO)%20of%20Prasar%20Bharati.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20public%20talk%2C%20I%20pointed%20to%20Sayani%20in%20the%20audience%20and%20mentioned%20why%20I%20considered%20him%20not%20only%20a%20fascinating%20entertainer%20%E2%80%94%20India%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20and%20first%20radio%20jockey%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20as%20someone%20who%20made%20a%20great%20yet%20unrecognised%20contribution%20in%20the%20cultural%20unification%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-message-id%3D%5C%22%23msg-f%3A1792322194253024273%5C%22%20data-legacy-message-id%3D%5C%2218df9b8a1f800c11%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20explained%20that%20by%20popularising%20Hindi%20film%20music%20on%20radio%20throughout%20the%20diverse%20and%20often-conflicting%20subcontinent%2C%20he%20helped%20in%20creating%20a%20common%20mass%20medium%20that%20everyone%20understood%20and%20loved.%C2%A0%20The%20entire%20hall%20of%20some%201500%20people%20suddenly%20got%20up%20to%20clap%2C%20spontaneously%2C%20as%20a%20tribute%20to%20Ameen%20sahab.%20He%2C%20too%2C%20rose%20from%20his%20seat%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20gesture%20and%20to%20take%20a%20bow.%20He%20wiped%20his%20spectacles%2C%20as%20his%20eyes%20may%20have%20been%20moist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20talk%2C%20I%20went%20straight%20from%20the%20podium%20to%20his%20seat.%20He%20hugged%20me%20and%20whispered%20that%20it%20was%20one%20of%20his%20finest%20hours.%20Though%20Ameen%C2%A0ji%20was%2085%2C%20he%20was%20so%20fit%20that%20I%20really%20never%20imagined%20then%20that%20this%20was%20the%20last%20time%20I%20would%20see%20him%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20do%20not%20know%20the%20full%20story%20%E2%80%94%20it%20began%20with%20his%20programme%20of%20introducing%20Hindi%20film%20music%20over%20Radio%20Ceylon%20in%20August%201952.%20India%20had%20emerged%20as%20one%20nation%20from%2014%20British%20Indian%20provinces%20and%20565%20kingdoms%20or%20different%20princely%20states%20only%20five%20years%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Frip-ameen-sayani-warm-voice-captivated-millions-of-listeners%5C%22%3ERIP%20Ameen%20Sayani%2C%20Whose%20Warm%20Voice%20Captivated%20Millions%20of%20Listeners%20for%20Generations%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhysically%2C%20the%20country%20was%20united%2C%20amidst%20partition%20riots%20and%20inter%20regional%20conflicts%20but%20it%20had%20neither%20a%20common%20language%20nor%20any%20real%20emotional%20unity.%20People%20spoke%20in%20hundreds%20of%20different%20languages%2C%20for%20English%20was%20only%20the%20language%20of%20the%20educated%2C%20but%20many%20regions%20resisted%20the%20imposition%20of%C2%A0%20strict%20Sanskritic%20Hindi%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20also%20the%20time%20when%20the%20Indian%20government%20had%20wanted%20people%20to%20listen%20only%20to%20high%20brow%20classical%20music%20and%20ghazals.%20The%20first%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%20B.V.%20Keskar%20branded%20Hindi%20film%20music%20as%20low-class%20%E2%80%98laralappa%E2%80%99%20and%20banned%20(yes%2C%20banned)%20Hindi%20film%20music%20over%20the%20monopoly%20radio%20network%2C%20All%20India%20Radio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParadoxically%2C%20it%20was%20also%20the%20golden%20era%20of%20Bollywood%20when%20its%20haunting%20music%20and%20exquisite%20lyrics%20and%20songs%20enraptured%20everyone.%20The%20masses%20were%2C%20therefore%2C%20thirsty%20for%20such%20popular%20music%20despite%20its%20ban%20over%20the%20national%20radio.%20Only%20a%20minuscule%20percentage%20owned%20expensive%20gramophones%20and%20very%20few%20could%20afford%20to%20go%20to%20cinema%20halls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201952%2C%20a%20Swiss%20company%20called%20CIBA%20(Chemische%20Industrie%20Basel)%20that%20sold%20Binaca%20toothpaste%20then%2C%20decided%20to%20sponsor%20a%20Hindi%20film%20music%20programme%20over%20Radio%20Ceylon.%20It%20was%20called%20Binaca%20Geetmala%20and%20Sayani%20was%20the%20%E2%80%98jockey%E2%80%99.%20His%20outstanding%20introductions%20and%20interventions%20soon%20made%20it%20a%20super%20hit%20parade%20of%20popular%20songs.%20He%20told%20me%20one%20day%2C%2060%20years%20later%2C%20while%20chatting%20in%20his%20little%20studio%20in%20Colaba%2C%20how%20he%20recorded%20each%20week%E2%80%99s%20show%20in%20Bombay%20(Mumbai%20now)%20itself%2C%20and%20how%20the%20spool%20was%20dispatched%20to%20Colombo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20broadcast%20from%208%20to%209%20pm%20every%20Wednesday.%20Since%20Ceylon%E2%80%99s%20British%20Second%20World%20War%20transmitters%20were%20very%20powerful%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20they%20were%20meant%20to%20reach%20war-ravaged%20Southeast%20Asia%20%E2%80%94%20Binaca%20Geetmala%20could%20be%20heard%20in%20most%20parts%20of%20India.%20It%20became%20so%20legendary%20that%20people%20stopped%20everything%20on%20Wednesday%20evenings%20to%20listen%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20imbibed%20the%20easy%20Hindustani%20language%2C%20that%20was%20peppered%20with%20Urdu%20romantic%20words%20and%20sweet%20colloquialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeskar%20and%20the%20mighty%20Akashvani%2C%20however%2C%20refused%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20people%20%E2%80%94%20even%20as%20Sayani%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20soared%20to%20dizzy%20heights.%20After%20five%20years%20of%20public%20criticism%20and%20resistance%2C%20All%20India%20Radio%20had%20to%20capitulate%20and%20began%20its%20own%20popular%20film%20music%20channel%2C%20called%20Vividh%20Bharati%20in%201957%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20Ameen%20ji%E2%80%99s%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20vast%20network%20and%20talented%20staff%20artistes%20and%20singers%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20who%20were%20from%20Bollywood%20%E2%80%94%20Akashvani%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20Vividh%20Bharati%20service%20played%20an%20ever%20better%20and%20more%20comprehensive%20role%20in%20uniting%20the%20entire%20country%20in%20one%20single%20voice.%20Vividh%20Bharati%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20programmes%20like%20Hawa%20Mahal%2C%20Jaimala%2C%20Aapki%20Farmaish%2C%20Bhoole%20Bisre%20Geet%2C%20Chitralok%2C%20Chayageet%20and%20the%20lot%20delighted%20Indians%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they%20liked%20kitabi%20(literary)%20Hindi%20or%20not.%20They%C2%A0%20bound%20together%20audiences%20from%20obscure%C2%A0%20Jhumritalaiyah%20to%20better%20known%20metros%20in%20one%20emotional%20family%20%E2%80%94%20more%20so%2C%20when%20transistors%20spread%20radio%20like%20wildfire%20in%20the%201960s.%20The%C2%A0%20cassette%20mania%20took%20over%2C%C2%A0%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20about%20Sayani%3F%20His%20later%20Colgate%20Cibaca%20Sangeetmala%20ran%20from%201954%20to%201994%20on%20Radio%20Ceylon%20and%20then%20he%20started%20doing%20programmes%20for%20Vividh%20Bharati%20%E2%80%94%20reaching%20out%20to%20more%20Indians%20and%20bonding%20them.%20He%20recorded%20some%C2%A0%2050%2C000%20radio%20programmes%20and%20gave%20his%20legendary%20voice%20to%20about%2020%2C000%20jingles.%20He%20also%20hosted%20TV%20shows%20and%20carried%20voiceovers%20and%20cameos%20in%20Hindi%20movies.%20But%2C%20it%20was%20his%20role%20as%20the%20one%20who%20catalysed%20the%20process%20of%20emotional%20unity%20among%20Indians%20which%20remains%20unique%20and%20really%20unforgettable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJawhar%20Sircar%C2%A0is%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20of%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress.%20He%20has%20been%20culture%20secretary%20in%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20CEO%20of%20Prasar%20Bharati.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709382540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F21200240%2FAmeen-Sayani.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fhow-ameen-sayani-helped-unite-the-soul-of-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20began%20with%20his%20programme%20of%20introducing%20Hindi%20film%20music%20over%20Radio%20Ceylon%20in%20August%201952.%20India%20had%20emerged%20as%20one%20nation%20from%2014%20British%20Indian%20provinces%20and%20565%20kingdoms%20or%20different%20princely%20states%20only%20five%20years%20earlier.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fhow-ameen-sayani-helped-unite-the-soul-of-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Europe's%20oldest%20monarch%20has%20pacemaker%20fit