-democracy%2Famp_articleshow%2F108153010.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20we%20tracked%20down%20the%20Ukrainian%20poison%20seller%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709351533000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F8319%2Fproduction%2F_132716533_zakutenko-index.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68413310%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Leonid%20Zakutenko%20sold%20poison%20to%20vulnerable%20people%20who%20wanted%20to%20die%20-%20we%20confronted%20him%20at%20a%20post%20office%20in%20Kyiv.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A52%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68413310%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68413310.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68413310.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Journalists%20Do%20Not%20Use%20Philosophy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01151944%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-3.19.20-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ENewspaper%20journalists%2C%20while%20writing%20on%20topics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F0003122419846628%5C%22%3Euse%20ideas%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20history%2C%20sociology%2C%20sciences%20and%20other%20disciplines%20to%20establish%20the%20relevance%20of%20a%20topic%20and%20analyse%20pertinent%20questions.%20Indian%20journalists%2C%20however%2C%20rarely%20seem%20to%20draw%20upon%20philosophical%20ideas%20despite%20being%20relevant%20to%20the%20discussion.%20For%20instance%2C%20moral%20philosophers%E2%80%99%20views%20are%20not%20used%20or%20presented%20in%20articles%20on%20social%20conflicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScience%20journalism%20mentions%20historical%20and%20sociological%20perspectives%20but%20does%20not%20include%20insights%20from%20the%20philosophy%20of%20science.%20The%20only%20kind%20of%20newspaper%20articles%20that%20draw%20from%20philosophy%20in%20India%20are%20opinion%20pieces%20written%20by%20a%20handful%20of%20philosophers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20that%20philosophy%20is%20glaringly%20absent%20in%20Indian%20newspaper%20journalism%20that%20otherwise%20seamlessly%20synthesises%20ideas%20from%20numerous%20disciplines%20while%20discussing%20a%20topic%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20non-engagement%20with%20philosophy%20is%20a%20characteristic%20of%20journalism%20across%20the%20world.%20Although%20there%20have%20been%20a%20few%20initiatives%20in%20the%20Global%20North%20to%20bridge%20this%20gap.%20Most%20of%20these%20have%20been%20confined%20to%20the%20opinion%20columns%20section%20of%20newspapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20well-known%20projects%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fcolumn%2Fthe-stone%5C%22%3EThe%20Stone%3C%2Fa%3E%20column%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20philosophy%20column%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Ftags%2Funthinkable%2F%5C%22%3EUnthinkable%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20run%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Irish%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Some%20philosophy%20foundations%20have%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarcsandersfoundation.org%2Fpublic-philosophy%2Fphilosophy-in-the-media%2F%5C%22%3Eprojects%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20enable%20philosophers%20to%20write%20for%20public%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBringing%20philosophy%20to%20journalism%20requires%20a%20proactive%20philosophy%20community.%20And%20this%20not%20happening%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%20%E2%80%94says%20something%20about%20the%20health%20of%20Indian%20academic%20philosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20aspect%20just%20accounts%20for%20Indian%20philosophers%20not%20writing%20for%20newspapers.%20It%20is%20still%20not%20clear%2C%20though%2C%20why%20Indian%20journalists%20are%20sidestepping%20philosophy.%20Are%20there%20any%20pragmatic%20constraints%20of%20the%20profession%20that%20filter%20out%20philosophical%20ideas%3F%20What%20presumptions%20of%20journalists%20about%20philosophy%20are%20at%20play%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPhilosophy%20is%20unknown%20and%20abstract%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20deputy%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EMukunth%20V%2C%20the%20main%20reason%20for%20the%20absence%20of%20philosophy%20in%20Indian%20newspapers%20is%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20unfamiliarity%20with%20the%20subject.%20This%20makes%20the%20journalists%E2%80%99%20job%20difficult%20to%20present%20pertinent%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20senior%20associate%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0Uddalak%20Mukherjee%20points%20out%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cantagonism%E2%80%9D%20of%20journalists%20towards%20scholarly%20work%20also%20contributes%20to%20the%20situation.%20This%20attitude%20is%20not%20without%20a%20cause.%20The%20jargonised%20academic%20discourse%20renders%20philosophy%20a%20subject%20that%20deals%20with%20%E2%80%9Cabstract%20ideals%20that%20have%20no%20practical%20applications%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProbably%20because%20of%20this%2C%20Jitesh%20Pandey%2C%20Mass%20Communication%20faculty%2C%20Karnavati%20University%20thinks%20philosophy%20cannot%20be%20articulated%20in%20a%20simple%20manner%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20diagnoses%20identify%20important%20challenges%20and%20also%20bring%20forth%20the%20vicious%20circle%20that%20perpetuates%20the%20problem.%20The%20underlying%20factor%20here%20is%20philosophy%20being%20specialised%20knowledge%20accessible%20only%20to%20a%20few%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20however%2C%20cannot%20be%20the%20only%20reason%20as%20other%20disciplines%20are%20equally%20technical%20and%20inaccessible.%20Why%20is%20it%20that%20journalists%2C%20who%20toil%20through%20other%20difficult%20ideas%2C%20do%20not%20put%20similar%20effort%20into%20philosophy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstance%20of%20a%20larger%20problem%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taylorfrancis.com%2Fchapters%2Fedit%2F10.4324%2F9781003039242-12%2Fcommunicating-social-sciences-humanities-angela-cassidy%5C%22%3Easymmetry%20in%20journalism%E2%80%99s%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20disciplines%20clarifies%20some%20aspects%20of%20the%20problem.%20News%20and%20research%20developments%20in%20sciences%20and%20some%20social%20science%20disciplines%20are%20reported%20more%20extensively%20than%20others.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20way%20disciplines%E2%80%99%20professionals%20and%20their%20work%20are%20portrayed%20in%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20scientists%20are%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9Cresearchers%E2%80%9D.%20In%20contrast%2C%20scholars%20of%20humanities%20and%20social%20sciences%20usually%20appear%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccommentators%20on%20pre-existing%20news%20stories%E2%80%9D.%20This%20distinction%20stems%20from%20the%20non-acknowledgement%20of%20the%20expertise%20in%20the%20concerned%20domains%2C%20as%20these%20disciplines%20are%20presumed%20to%20study%20everyday%20activities%20and%20phenomena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoving%20from%20the%20communication%20of%20disciplines%20to%20their%20uses%20in%20journalism%2C%20another%20preference%20can%20be%20noticed.%20Journalism%20has%20gradually%20come%20to%20use%20social%20science%20methods%20and%20ideas%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20news.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fpoq%2Farticle-abstract%2F44%2F4%2F477%2F1847364%5C%22%3EThis%20way%20of%20doing%20journalism%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0started%20some%20decades%20back%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20not%20just%20reporting%20but%20interpreting%20the%20news%20as%20well.%20This%20development%20also%20correlates%20with%20the%20steady%20increase%20of%20social%20scientists%20appearing%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F0963662517693452%5C%22%3Eexpert%20commentators%20on%20general%20news%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20features%20of%20contemporary%20journalism%20explain%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20philosophy.%20Given%20that%20humanities%20is%20on%20the%20periphery%20of%20journalism%E2%80%99s%20coverage%20radar%2C%20philosophy%20events%20will%20hardly%20be%20considered%20newsworthy.%20More%20importantly%2C%20having%20evolved%20to%20use%20social%20sciences%20techniques%2C%20journalism%20would%20not%20be%20interested%20in%20queries%20for%20which%20philosophy%20can%20provide%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fgandhi-and-the-future-of-slow-philosophy%5C%22%3EGandhi%20and%20the%20Future%20of%20Slow%20Philosophy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fosf.io%2Fpreprints%2Fsocarxiv%2Fzeh9t%5C%22%3Erecent%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20science%20journalism%20practice%20in%20India%20substantiates%20these%20observations.%20Among%20the%20topics%20covered%20by%20Indian%20science%20journalists%2C%20%E2%80%9CPhilosophy%20of%20Science%E2%80%9D%20is%20absent.%20However%2C%20%E2%80%9CScience%20and%20Society%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CHistory%20of%20Science%E2%80%9D%20are%20among%20the%20dominant%20topics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnfamiliarity%20and%20omissions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhilosophy%E2%80%99s%20absence%20in%20journalism%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20journalism%20education.%20The%20BA%20and%20PG%20diploma%20programmes%20on%20mass%20communication%2C%20as%20Pandey%20attests%2C%20dominantly%20focus%20on%20technical%20skills.%20The%20remaining%20quota%20for%20theoretical%20courses%20in%20the%20syllabi%20only%20covers%20some%20social%20science%20topics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAman%20Khanna%2C%20senior%20associate%20editor%2C%20%3Cem%3EScroll%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20cautions%20that%20not%20all%20journalists%20have%20a%20journalism%20degree.%20Since%20people%20from%20various%20educational%20backgrounds%20enter%20the%20profession%2C%20school%20curricula%20not%20having%20philosophy%20need%20to%20be%20factored%20in.%20Also%2C%20Khanna%20thinks%20that%20there%20might%20not%20be%20many%20philosophy%20graduates%20doing%20journalism.%20Even%20if%20there%20are%20only%20a%20few%2C%20whether%20they%20are%20implementing%20their%20philosophy%20training%20in%20the%20work%20remains%20to%20be%20explored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20journalists%20are%20largely%20ignorant%20of%20philosophy%2C%20they%20can%20hardly%20be%20blamed%20for%20not%20drawing%20from%20it.%20Sayantan%20Datta%2C%20science%20journalist%20and%20faculty%2C%20Krea%20University%2C%20however%2C%20mentions%20instances%20where%20philosophy%20is%20invisibilised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%20journalists%20use%20philosophical%20ideas%20unknowingly%20but%20do%20not%20acknowledge%20them%20as%20they%20do%20not%20put%20the%20effort%20to%20trace%20their%20origin.%20In%20other%20cases%2C%20the%20ideas%20involved%20during%20the%20framing%20of%20an%20article%20get%20buried%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cangle%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20article%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20told%2C%20but%20shown%E2%80%9D.%20These%20kinds%20of%20omissions%20are%20of%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContrasting%20conceptions%20of%20philosophy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unfamiliarity%20with%20the%20discipline%20has%20cultivated%20two%20contrasting%20images%20of%20philosophy%20in%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20journalists%2C%20who%20acknowledge%20that%20philosophy%20is%20not%20explicitly%20used%2C%20add%20that%20journalism%20implicitly%20involves%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mukunth%2C%20journalists%20are%20employing%20philosophy%20when%20deciding%20the%20basics%20%E2%80%93%20what%2C%20why%20and%20how%20%E2%80%93%20of%20a%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShubashree%20Desikan%2C%20adjunct%20faculty%2C%20Asian%20College%20of%20Journalism%20believes%20that%20philosophy%20is%20present%20%E2%80%9Cimplicitly%20in%20the%20practice%20and%20teaching%E2%80%9D%20of%20science%20journalism.%20Especially%2C%20knowing%20the%20science%20required%20for%20an%20article%20demands%20understanding%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunderlying%20philosophy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhilosophy%2C%20as%20a%20discipline%2C%20does%20study%20things%20%E2%80%93%20like%20reasoning%20and%20foundations%20of%20science%20%E2%80%93%20that%20are%20integral%20to%20journalism%20practice.%20But%20someone%20merely%20doing%20these%20does%20not%20imply%20they%20are%20using%20philosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20even%20though%20science%20explains%20how%20a%20ball%20moves%2C%20someone%20need%20not%20be%20using%20it%20whenever%20they%20throw%20the%20ball.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20philosophy%2C%20this%20kind%20of%20confusion%20happens%20when%20the%20discipline%20and%20its%20ideas%20are%20not%20distinguished%20from%20other%20colloquial%20meanings%20of%20%E2%80%9Cphilosophy%E2%80%9D%2C%20like%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merriam-webster.com%2Fdictionary%2Fphilosophy%5C%22%3Ethe%20most%20basic%20beliefs%2C%20concepts%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMukherjee%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20thinks%20opinion%20columns%20are%20more%20amenable%20for%20philosophy%20articles%20as%20they%20provide%20the%20space%20for%20%E2%80%9Cdeeper%20engagement%E2%80%9D.%20Similarly%2C%20Mukunth%20opines%20that%20magazines%2C%20unlike%20newspapers%2C%20provide%20the%20required%20space%20and%20time%20for%20philosophical%20deliberations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20suggestions%20though%20arising%20from%20pragmatic%20concerns%20presume%20that%20the%20articulation%20of%20philosophical%20ideas%20usually%20requires%20detailed%20discussions%20and%20that%20these%20ideas%20are%20relevant%20only%20for%20an%20in-depth%20examination%20of%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20these%20two%20extreme%20conceptions%20of%20philosophy%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20current%20state%20of%20affairs.%20On%20one%20side%2C%20the%20bare%20conception%20of%20philosophy%20reduces%20it%20to%20aspects%20implicitly%20present%20everywhere%20and%20hence%2C%20obvious%20to%20mention.%20Contrary%20to%20this%2C%20its%20conception%20as%20a%20specialised%20knowledge%20makes%20philosophical%20ideas%20elusive%2C%20hard%20and%20better%20restricted%20to%20opinion%20articles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20way%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20journalism%E2%80%99s%20role%20is%20just%20to%20observe%20and%20report%2C%20then%20the%20philosophy%E2%80%99s%20absence%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20as%20journalism%20is%20merely%20mirroring%20its%20absence%20in%20society.%20However%2C%20when%20journalism%20is%20construed%20to%20be%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F17512786.2018.1473041%5C%22%3Ecollaborative%2C%20radical%20and%20constructive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20can%20address%20the%20absence%20within%20and%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20philosophical%20ideas%20are%20presently%20confined%20to%20opinion%20articles%2C%20having%20dedicated%20philosophy%20columns%2C%20like%20the%20one%20edited%20by%20Mukherjee%20at%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20will%20give%20the%20required%20initial%20push.%20Philosophy%20articles%20have%20steadily%20increased%20in%20Indian%20platforms%2C%20primarily%20due%20to%20the%20trend%20of%20republishing%20from%20international%20websites.%20Instead%20of%20this%2C%20editors%20can%20collaborate%20with%20Indian%20scholars%20and%20foster%20a%20community%20of%20philosophers%20who%20can%20write%20for%20newspapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20philosophy%20to%20eventually%20be%20used%20in%20mainstream%20journalism%20practice%2C%20journalists%20need%20to%20become%20familiar%20with%20it.%20Without%20that%2C%20philosophy%20will%20remain%20dual-faced%2C%20both%20trivial%20and%20extraordinary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVarun%20S.%20Bhatta%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Philosophy%20at%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20Education%20and%20Research%20Bhopal.%20He%20is%20the%20co-moderator%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indianphilosophynetwork.org%2F%5C%22%3EIndian%20Philosophy%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.barefootphilosophers.com%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3EThe%20views%20expressed%20in%20the%20article%20by%20the%20author%20and%20the%20respondents%20are%20personal%20opinions%20and%20are%20not%20of%20their%20respective%20institutions.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709350233000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01151944%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-3.19.20-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fwhy-journalists-do-not-use-philosophy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20of%20the%20well-known%20projects%20was%20The%20Stone%20column%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%20The%20philosophy%20column%20called%20Unthinkable%20is%20still%20run%20by%20The%20Irish%20Times.%20Some%20philosophy%20foundations%20have%20started%20projects%20to%20enable%20philosophers%20to%20write%20for%20public%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fwhy-journalists-do-not-use-philosophy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Not%20AI%20but%20this%20is%20far%20bigger%20threat%20to%20mankind%3A%20Italian%20defence%20company%20CEO%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709349196000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108152056%2Cimgsize-1548597.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fnot-ai-but-this-is-a-far-bigger-threat-to-mankind-says-italian-defence-company-ceo%2Farticleshow%2F108152081.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Leonardo's%20CEO%20downplays%20fear%20surrounding%20AI%20as%20a%20tool%20controlled%20by%20humans.%20Despite%20this%2C%20Leonardo%20plans%20a%20significant%20technological%20shift%20with%20autonomous%20systems%20powered%20by%20AI.%20Industry%20giants%20in%20AITech%20call%20for%20regulation%20and%20responsible%20development.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fnot-ai-but-this-is-a-far-bigger-threat-to-mankind-says-italian-defence-company-ceo%2Farticleshow%2F108152081.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Contemporary%20Hindi%20Literature%20Tells%20Us%20About%20the%20Politics%20of%20Hate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26130445%2FIMG_2925-3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBen%20Okri%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CStorytellers%20are%20the%20singing%20conscience%20of%20a%20land%2C%20the%20unacknowledged%20guides.%E2%80%9D%20For%20him%2C%20the%20life%20of%20a%20nation%20%E2%80%93%20its%20health%2C%20its%20spiritual%20strength%20%E2%80%93%20can%20be%20deduced%20from%20the%20stories%20the%20nation%20tells%2C%20the%20stories%20it%20suppresses%2C%20the%20stories%20it%20sanctions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnlike%20historians%20who%20work%20with%20the%20past%3B%20the%20storyteller%E2%80%99s%20job%20is%20to%20weave%20individual%20sufferings%20into%20the%20fabric%20of%20time%2C%20connecting%20the%20past%2C%20the%20present%20and%20the%20future.%20History%20mostly%20revolves%20around%20leaders%2C%20winners%2C%20kings.%20It%20condenses%20individual%20grief%20and%20trauma%20in%20objective%20reports%20and%20cold%20statistics.%20But%20for%20the%20storyteller%2C%20ordinary%20suffering%20is%20supreme.%20In%20violent%20times%20like%20the%20Partition%2C%20war%2C%20communal%20riots%2C%20the%20voices%20that%20get%20erased%20due%20to%20fear%20and%20circumstance%2C%20and%20the%20experiences%20that%20are%20reduced%20to%20footnotes%20form%20the%20writers%E2%80%99%20material.%20Their%20task%20is%20to%20observe%2C%20listen%20and%20put%20the%20unspeakable%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20wonder%2C%20literature%20remains%20the%20place%20where%20ordinary%20grief%2C%20disenchantment%2C%20and%20suffering%20get%20the%20fundamental%20dignity%20of%20being%20recorded%20and%20memorialised.%20That%20literature%20became%20an%20important%20way%20to%20memorialise%20the%20bewildering%20rupture%20of%20Partition%20is%20significant.%20It%20is%20also%20significant%20that%20more%20than%20English%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebhashas%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EHindi%2C%20Urdu%2C%20Bangla%20%E2%80%93%20spoke%20most%20eloquently%20about%20Partition%20horrors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMother%20tongues%20are%20the%20languages%20of%20our%20dreams%20and%20our%20mourning.%20Noted%20historian%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25817920%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EMushirul%20Hasan%20says%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Partition%20literatures%20constitute%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6a%20cultural%20archive%20of%20first-hand%20information%2C%20experiences%20and%20vivid%20impressions..%E2%80%9D%20without%20which%2C%20the%20anguish%2C%20uncertainty%2C%20loss%2C%20confusion%20faced%20by%20those%20afflicted%2C%20can%20never%20be%20understood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hansrajcollege.ac.in%2FhCPanel%2Fuploads%2Felearning%2Felearning_document%2F(Contemporary_South_Asia)_Gyanendra_Pandey_-_Remembering_Partition__Violence%2C_Nationalism_and_History_in_India-Cambridge_University_Press_(2002).pdf%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EGyanendra%20Pandey%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESubaltern%20School%20of%20Humanities%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20calls%20the%20inability%20of%20History%20to%20record%20ordinary%20suffering%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20chasm%20between%20history%20and%20memory.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESubaltern%20School%20of%20Humanities%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20founded%20by%20Ranajit%20Guha%2C%20Shahid%20Amin%2C%20Gyanendra%20Pandey%20and%20others%2C%20asserts%20that%20this%20chasm%20can%20be%20bridged%20only%20by%20dipping%20into%20oral%20histories%2C%20written%20first%20person%20accounts%2C%20songs%2C%20folklore%20and%20literature%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20emotional%20and%20psychological%20echoes%20of%20collective%20violence%20continue%20to%20reverberate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20preface%20to%20the%20four%20volume%20anthology%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EStories%20about%20the%20Partition%20of%20India%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4408572%3FsearchText%3Dalok%2520Bhalla%2520partition%26searchUri%3D%252Faction%252FdoBasicSearch%253FQuery%253Dalok%252BBhalla%252Bpartition%26ab_segments%3D0%252Fbasic_search_gsv2%252Fcontrol%26refreqid%3Dfastly-default%253Abd3897e034b4ee99558462b86c5b08b3%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EAlok%20Bhalla%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CPartition%20fictions%20bears%20witness%20to%20the%20sorrows%20of%20the%20exiled%E2%80%A6but%20refuse%20to%20surrender%20to%20any%20bullying%20ideology%E2%80%A6.there%20are%20hardly%20any%20communally%20charged%20stories%20preaching%20hate%20and%20calling%20for%20annihilation%20of%20other%20religious%20groups%20written%20in%20any%20of%20the%20languages%20of%20the%20subcontinent.%E2%80%9D%20Hindi-Urdu%20novelists%20of%20post%20partition%20era%20%E2%80%93%20Bhishm%20Sahani%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETamas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Rahi%20Masoom%20Raza%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAdha%20Gaon%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Yashpal%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJhootha%20Sach%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Krishna%20Sobti%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZindaginama%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Gujarat%20Pakistan%20se%20Gujarat%20Hindustan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Amrita%20Pritam%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPinjar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Rajinder%20Bedi%2C%20Kartar%20Singh%20Duggal%2C%20Joginder%20Paul%2C%20Rajee%20Seth%2C%20Intizar%20Hussain%2C%20and%20Qurratulain%20Hyder%20%E2%80%93%20likewise%20chronicle%20the%20violence%2C%20the%20silence%2C%20and%20the%20trauma%2C%20along%20with%20the%20loss%2C%20the%20bewilderment.%20This%20literary%20feast%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20given%20that%20modernist%20Hindi-Urdu%20literature%20came%20of%20age%20in%20the%20early%20decades%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20and%20determined%20its%20role%20through%20the%20founding%20of%20the%20Progressive%20Writer%E2%80%99s%20Group%20or%20PWG%2C%20in%201935%2C%20by%20Premchand%2C%20Nirala%2C%20Manto%2C%20Chugtai%20and%20several%20others.%20This%20ethos%20of%20%E2%80%9Ca%20critical%20engagement%20with%20the%20political-social%20upheavals%20of%20the%20time%E2%80%9D%20has%20influenced%20subsequent%20generations%20of%20writers%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EContemporary%20Hindi%20literature%20constitutes%20an%20archive%20of%20experiences%20of%20contemporary%20religion%2C%20caste%2C%20gender%20and%20ecological%20violences.%20It%20catalogues%20the%20effect%20of%20violent%20public%20discourse%20on%20private%20spaces%20and%20on%20individual%20psyches.%20They%20talk%20of%20channels%20of%20greed%20irrigated%20by%20violent%20discourse.%20Between%20their%20pages%2C%20individual%20anxiety%2C%20grief%2C%20social%20uncertainty%20and%20absurdity%20get%20a%20place%20to%20be.%20They%20link%20economic%20liberalisation%20with%20the%20politics%20incubated%20by%20it.%20They%20show%20how%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20bogey%20enemy%20is%20essential%20to%20corral%20and%20fence%20off%20of%20the%20financial%20gains%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20patriarchy%20and%20caste%20hegemonies%20stay%20intact.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EInvasion%20of%20politics%20in%20intimate%20spaces%20in%20Geetanjali%20Shree%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHamara%20Shahar%20Us%20Baras%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20started%20talking%20as%20if%20there%20really%20were%20only%20two%20identities%20and%20everything%20was%20either%20Hindu%20or%20Muslim.%E2%80%9D%20(translation%20mine.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGeetanjali%20Shree%E2%80%99s%20narrator%20in%20this%20novel%2C%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20%E2%80%98that%20year%E2%80%99%20when%20her%20city%20starts%20witnessing%20frequent%20communal%20disturbances.%20A%20time%20of%20uncertainty%20and%20dread%20when%20the%20old%20and%20tried%20and%20tested%20ways%20of%20living%20got%20kicked%20aside.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENarrated%20in%20a%20breathless%2C%20fragmented%20voice%20by%20a%20narrator%20who%20says%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20writer%20but%20someone%20who%20is%20simply%20taking%20down%20whatever%20people%20say%2C%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20style%20mimics%20the%20external%20situation%20of%20the%20fragmentation%20in%20the%20city.%20The%20focus%20is%20not%20on%20incidents%2C%20but%20on%20fleshing%20out%20the%20shocked%20silence%2C%20the%20paralytic%20huddle%20of%20intellectuals%2C%20and%20the%20tongue-tied%20incomprehension%20of%20professional%20writers%20who%20do%20not%20know%20how%20to%20respond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20year%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Hindus%20left%20amicability.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Jagdambe%20Math%20that%20lay%20hidden%20in%20a%20shrubbery%20on%20one%20side%20of%20a%20playground%20across%20from%20their%20balcony%2C%20emerged%20from%20the%20shrubbery%20%E2%80%93%20first%20with%20a%20saffron%20flag%20on%20top%2C%20then%20with%20a%20mela%2C%20then%20a%20loudspeaker%2C%20that%20got%20louder%20and%20louder%20in%20its%20chants%20and%20slogans%20%E2%80%93%20and%20started%20marching%20over%20the%20playground.%20The%20narrator%20who%20is%20neither%20a%20professor%20nor%20an%20intellectual%20like%20her%20friends%2C%20goes%20on%20trying%20to%20write%20how%20the%20events%20outside%20are%20wrecking%20the%20most%20intimate%20and%20sacred%20parts%20of%20them.%20Whether%20they%20talk%20or%20studiously%20avoid%20talking%20of%20events%2C%20Shruti%20and%20Hanif%2C%20the%20interfaith%20couple%2C%20and%20Sharad%20and%20Hanif%20colleagues%20and%20friends%2C%20find%20the%20air%20between%20them%20vitiated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20derailment%20of%20ordinary%20lives%20in%20Rakesh%20Kayasth%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3ERambhakt%20Rangbaz%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESet%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20imminent%20rath%20yatra%20in%20a%20small%20town%20mohalla%20Aramganj%2C%20the%20novel%20deconstructs%20Mandal-Kamandal%20politics%20of%20the%20heartland%20through%20the%20story%20of%20a%20popular%20Ram%20worshipping%20Muslim%20tailor%2C%20Ashiq%20Rangbaz%2C%20whose%20life%20is%20thrown%20into%20chaos%20as%20an%20altered%20discourse%20takes%20over%20the%20mohalla.%20People%20he%20has%20been%20with%20all%20his%20life%2C%20suddenly%20start%20asking%20new%20questions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAkhilesh%20had%20asked%20on%20his%20face%2C%20%E2%80%98We%20all%20think%20of%20you%20as%20a%20Hindu.%20Who%20do%20you%20think%20you%20are%2C%20bey%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20answer%20came%2C%20%E2%80%98Whatever%20my%20Ram%20ji%20has%20made%20me%2C%20I%20am%20that%20only.%20Why%20do%20you%20take%20tension%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Meaning%2C%20Ram%20ji%20made%20you%20a%20mulla%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Yes%2C%20think%20that%20only.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIncredible%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20things%20you%20say.%20Is%20that%20even%20possible%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98When%20a%20chutiya%20like%20you%20can%20be%20made%20by%20Ram%20ji%2C%20then%20why%20not%20me%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20trap%20Rangbaz%20with%20mere%20questions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20so%2C%20why%20at%20all%20are%20these%20questions%20being%20asked%3F%20Why%20has%20their%20frequency%20gone%20up%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%3F%20Aramganj%20walas%20do%20not%20know%20why%2C%20but%20they%20suddenly%20have%20too%20many%20questions%20about%20Muslims%20in%20their%20hearts.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E(translation%20mine)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Greek%20chorus%20of%20small%20town%20characters%20and%20their%20antics%20reveal%20diverse%20views%20on%20the%20emerging%20politics.%20It%20is%20not%20as%20though%20communal%20mindsets%20did%20not%20exist%20earlier%20in%20this%20mohalla%20beset%20with%20feudal%2C%20patriarchal%20and%20casteist%20characters%3B%20but%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esuddenly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20they%20acquire%20a%20rallying%20point%20and%20a%20face.%20The%20real%20question%20is%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20whether%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20newfound%20Hindu%20unity%20imply%20an%20end%20of%20caste-divisions%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esimply%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20scuttling%20of%20caste%20politics%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUday%20Prakash%3A%20The%20absurd%20face%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20growth%20story%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20contemporary%20Hindi%20writer%20better%20captures%20the%20cauldron%20of%20desperate%20inequity%20that%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economy%20and%20world%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20largest%20consumer%20market%20is%2C%20than%20Uday%20Prakash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20translator%20Jason%20Grunebaum%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CTo%20read%20Uday%20Prakash%20is%20to%20witness%20profound%20displacement.%20It%20is%20a%20displacement%20unleashed%20by%20forces%20both%20imported%20and%20indigenous%2C%20in%20the%20India%20of%20today%20%E2%80%93%20global%2C%20hungry%2C%20late-stage%20capitalism%20steeped%20in%20centuries-old%20caste%20oppression%20%E2%80%93%20inscribed%20on%20the%20likes%20of%20sweepers%2C%20weavers%2C%20semi-retired%20judges%2C%20typesetters%2C%20servants%20returned%20from%20the%20dead%2C%20sick%20slum%20kids%2C%20and%20others%20unable%2C%20or%20unwilling%2C%20to%20fall%20in%20line.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrakash%E2%80%99s%20surreal%20dystopias%20string%20together%20news%20headlines%2C%20history%20and%20poetry.%20There%20is%20no%20justice%2C%20poetic%20or%20otherwise%20in%20the%20economic%20dystopias%20of%20those%20living%20in%20slums%20and%20footpaths%20of%20society.%20Life%20is%20cheap%2C%20people%20are%20always%20dying.%20They%20drink%20discarded%20poison%20syrups%20and%20die%2C%20get%20killed%20in%20encounter%20killings%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETepchu%2C%20Dilli%20ki%20Diwar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20commit%20suicide%20due%20to%20caste%20oppression%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMohandas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20die%20screaming%20when%20forced%20to%20doctor%20post-mortem%20reports%2C%20or%20simply%20vanish.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20spiffy%2C%20beautified%2C%20segregated%20city%2C%20in%20Geetanjali%20Shree%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EYahan%20Haathi%20Rahte%20The%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20young%20employee%20in%20a%20multinational%20is%20intrigued%20by%20the%20figure%20of%20an%20old%20lady%20who%20he%20often%20comes%20across%20on%20the%20beautified%20promenade.%20Once%20elephants%20bathed%20on%20ghats%20where%20this%20promenade%20now%20exists.%20Who%20is%20she%3F%20From%20which%20part%20of%20the%20city%3F%20This%20side%20or%20that%20side%3F%20After%20the%20riots%2C%20the%20spiffy%20city%20has%20been%20split%20in%20two.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20riots%20made%20this%20city%20famous.%20Well%2C%20not%20the%20riots%20themselves%2C%20but%20the%20glitter%20and%20glamor%20that%20most%20definitely%20resulted%20from%20the%20riots.%20Had%20the%20city%20not%20been%20so%20jammed%20and%20jumbled%2C%20chaos%20would%20not%20have%20broken%20out.%20And%20if%20chaos%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20broken%20out%2C%20there%20would%20never%20have%20been%20such%20a%20cleanup.%20The%20factions%20were%20divided%20so%20neatly%20the%20city%20shone.%20One%20faction%20this%20side%20of%20the%20river%2C%20one%20that%20side%2C%20and%20each%20clearly%20recognizable%20in%20its%20place.%20As%20though%20factories%20had%20been%20built%20on%20either%20side%20to%20manufacture%20each%20faction%E2%80%99s%20particular%20costumes%20and%20masks%2C%20and%20absolutely%20everyone%20appeared%20only%20in%20their%20respective%20attire.%20Everyone%20wore%20their%20assigned%20uniform%2C%20and%20everyone%20wore%20the%20same%20mask.%20This%20side%20wore%20theirs%2C%20that%20side%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eore%20theirs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwordswithoutborders.org%2Fread%2Farticle%2F2023-01%2Fonce-elephants-lived-here-part-one-geetanjali-shree-daisy-rockwell%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETranslation%20by%20Daisy%20Rockwell.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20found%20glamour%20of%20malls%2C%20high-rises%20and%20multiplexes%20sits%20on%20the%20ruins%20of%20the%20chaotic%2C%20composite%2C%20open-armed%20city%20that%20was.%20Even%20the%20plate-glassed%20office%20where%20the%20protagonist%20works%2C%20was%20once%20a%20haveli%20belonging%20to%20the%20same%20old%20woman%20whose%20bold%20craziness%20makes%20the%20homogenized%20new%20world%20uneasy.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETerrorizing%20any%20designated%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20to%20appropriate%20their%20land%20and%20Capital%20for%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98beautification%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20prerequisite%20for%20such%20selective%2C%20sterile%20growth.%20The%20true%20face%20of%20neoliberal%20capitalistic%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%C2%A0%20is%20made%20visible%20in%20this%20story%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPortraits%20of%20neoliberal%20paranoia%3A%20Chandan%20Pandey%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3E%20Vaidhanik%20Galp%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%20(translated%2C%20%E2%80%98Legal%20Fiction%E2%80%99)%20and%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EKeertigaan%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELegal%20Fiction%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20first%20of%20Chandan%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98New%20India%E2%80%99%20trilogy%2C%20picks%20the%20seams%20of%20a%20love%20jihad%20plot%20set%20in%20small%20town%20eastern%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20The%20narrator%20Arjun%E2%80%99s%20encounter%20with%20the%20police%2C%20bureaucracy%20and%20local%20politics%20in%20Noma%20%E2%80%93%20where%20he%20has%20flown%20to%20help%20his%20ex-friend%20trace%20her%20missing%20husband%2C%20a%20Muslim%20professor%20in%20a%20local%20college%20%E2%80%93%20soon%20turns%20Kafkaesque.%20Nothing%20here%20is%20what%20it%20seems%2C%20and%20everyone%20from%20the%20police%20to%20local%20politicians%20work%20as%20one%3A%20so%20that%20victim%20becomes%20aggressor%2C%20complaint%2C%20confession.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthirdlanemag.com%2Fin-conversation-chandan-pandey-speaks-to-varsha-tiwary-on-keertigaan%2Fnon-fiction%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKeertigan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20second%20in%20the%20series%2C%20portrays%20the%20trauma%20of%20mob%20lynching%20through%20the%20narrative%20of%20two%20journalists%2C%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman%2C%20who%20are%20travelling%20across%20north%20India%20to%20collect%20testimonies%20of%20mob%20lynching%20victims%20and%20their%20families.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20collecting%20the%20horrific%20testimonies%20and%20over%20encounters%20with%20strutting%20culprits%2C%20the%20troubled%20male%20journalist%20starts%20seeing%20lynched%20men%20everywhere.%20They%20whisper%20to%20him%20in%20conference%20rooms%2C%20their%20family%20members%20haunt%20his%20dreams.%20As%20disjointed%20memories%20of%20violence%2C%20the%20helplessness%20of%20victims%2C%20their%20echoing%2C%20pleading%20voices%20and%20testimonies%20lay%20siege%20to%20his%20mind%2C%20he%20disintegrates.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECows%20and%20tribal%20politics%3A%20Anil%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EGausevak%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnil%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20novella%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGausevak%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20portrays%20how%20political%20patronage%20has%20overturned%20the%20earlier%20solidarities%20of%20workers%20and%20downtrodden.%20Now%2C%20the%20tribals%20must%20either%20get%20%E2%80%9Cintegrated%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20system%E2%80%9D%20or%20get%20killed%20in%20encounters.%20An%20ordinary%20college%20going%20tribal%20youth%20Dhama%20Chero%2C%20manages%20to%20become%20a%20local%20panchayat%20level%20leader%2C%20and%20then%20dons%20the%20mantle%20of%20a%20cow%20protector%2C%20hoping%20it%20will%20enable%20him%20to%20get%20Hindu%20Party%20ticket%20to%20contest%20MLA%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20the%20blessings%20of%20the%20Goddess%20of%20Greed%2C%20a%20stiff%20competition%20went%20on%20among%20the%20police%20to%20extort%20more%2C%20and%20the%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecattle%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20traders%2C%20to%20save%20more.%20The%20traders%20found%20newer%20ways%20to%20cross%20the%20police%20barriers%2C%20while%20the%20police%20tried%20to%20enter%20as%20many%20trucks%20as%20possible%20to%20check%20health%20documents%20of%20the%20animals%20and%20the%20arrangements%20for%20their%20fodder%20and%20water.%20Any%20laxity%20led%20to%20a%20case%20lodged%20under%20specific%20clauses%20of%20Prevention%20of%20Cruelty%20to%20Animals%20Act%2C%20due%20to%20which%20the%20animals%20were%20held%20back%20for%20a%20few%20days.%20But%20the%20business%20never%20stopped.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20work%20for%20the%20country%20on%20a%20more%20dependable%20basis%2C%20Dhama%20Chero%20had%2C%20thanks%20to%20his%20politics%2C%20set%20up%20a%20cow-shelter%2C%20and%20was%20now%20a%20registered%20cow-protector%2C%20%E2%80%9Cgausevak.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mechanics%20that%20connect%20cow%20politics%20to%20upward%20mobility%20and%20quick%20profits%20are%20laid%20bare.%20Opting%20out%20of%20this%20politics%20can%20reduce%20a%20man%20to%20mere%20fodder%20in%20the%20perpetual%20brutal%20struggle%20between%20the%20State%20and%20the%20Naxalites.%20And%20yet%2C%20the%20price%20of%20co-option%20also%20keeps%20getting%20raised%20for%20ambitious%20youth%20like%20Dhama%20Chero.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20these%20Hindi%20novels%2C%20the%20eye%20watching%20the%20march%20of%20events%20is%20not%20that%20of%20a%20baffled%20outsider%2C%20but%20of%20an%20insider%3B%20of%20someone%20caught%20in%20a%20nightmare%20they%20have%20no%20ability%20to%20control.%20Like%20Partition%20narratives%2C%20these%20stories%20record%2C%20bear%20witness%2C%20and%20also%20lament%20for%20simpler%2C%20more%20innocent%20times%20when%20all%20shades%20of%20humanity%20could%20exist%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%20way.%20With%20courage%20and%20forthrightness%2C%20they%20perform%20the%20first%20duty%20of%20literature%3A%20%E2%80%9CTo%20tell%20us%20the%20truth%20about%20ourselves%20by%20telling%20us%20lies%20about%20other%20people.%E2%80%9D%20They%20create%20not%20just%20psychic%20spaces%2C%20but%20initiate%20a%20much%20needed%20moral%20discourse%20about%20experiences%20that%20get%20buried%20in%20the%20noise%20of%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERashwita%20Ravy%20is%20the%20pen%20name%20of%20the%20author%2C%20a%20literature%20lover.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709346611000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26130445%2FIMG_2925-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhat-contemporary-hindi-literature-tells-us-about-the-politics-of-hate%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Between%20their%20pages%2C%20individual%20anxiety%2C%20grief%2C%20social%20uncertainty%20and%20absurdity%20get%20a%20place%20to%20be.%20These%20books%20show%20us%20how%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20bogey%20of%20an%20enemy%20is%20essential%20to%20ensure%20that%20patriarchy%20and%20caste%20hegemonies%20stay%20intact.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhat-contemporary-hindi-literature-tells-us-about-the-politics-of-hate%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kaylen%20Ng%20Wins%202024%20Deutsche%20Bank%20Frieze%20Los%20Angeles%20Film%20Award%2C%20Britt%20Williams%20Lands%20Audience%20Award%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709346600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Ffrieze.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D562%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235928085%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kaylen%20Ng%C2%A0was%20named%20as%20the%20recipient%20of%20the%20%2410%2C000%20Deutsche%20Bank%20Frieze%20Los%20Angeles%20Film%20Award%20on%20Friday%20at%20the%20renowned%20