or%20a%20long%20time%20now%2C%20however%2C%20even%20the%20most%20beautiful%20and%20popular%20tourist%20destinations%20%E2%80%93%20which%20one%20might%20assume%20are%20the%20most%20protected%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20world%20seem%20to%20be%20choking%20by%20the%20surge%20of%20plastic%20and%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20named%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsrinagar.nic.in%2Ftourist-place%2Fdal-lake%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CJewel%20in%20the%20crown%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%2C%20is%20drowning%20in%20municipal%20sewage%2C%20and%20pollution%2C%20covered%20with%20weeds%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fgallery%2F2021%2F9%2F23%2Fkashmir-dal-lake-weeds-sewage-environment-pollution%5C%22%3Epatches%20of%20garbage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%C2%A0people%20(those%20living%20in%20houseboats)%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20urbanisation.%20Thanks%20to%20the%20rapid%20commercialisation%20of%20the%20surrounding%20region%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20just%20paying%20through%20their%20wages%20and%20house%2C%20but%20also%20through%20their%20self.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20unravelling%20causes%20of%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20pollution%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Dal%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20fish.%20But%20this%20sewage%20has%20destroyed%20the%20fish.%20All%20the%20garbage%20goes%20into%20the%20Dal.%20We%20used%20to%20drink%20this%20water%2C%20but%20today%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20wash%20your%20face%20with%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Javed%20Ahmed%2C%20a%20fisherman%20who%20was%20relocated%20to%20the%20fisherman%20colony%20in%20Habbak%2C%20an%20area%20%3Cspan%3Ein%20the%20vicinity%20of%20the%20Dal%20Lake.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20sewage%20and%20pollution%20in%20the%20Dal%20has%20been%20a%20well-documented%20phenomenon%20for%20a%20few%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirobserver.net%2F2020%2F03%2F02%2F70-of-srinagars-sewerage-goes-into-dal-lake-experts%2F%5C%22%3E%20years%20now%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcademic%20and%20scientific%20work%20has%20been%20uncovering%20the%20causes%20of%20pollution%20and%20its%20permanent%20impacts.%20Noteworthy%20transformations%20occurred%20in%20the%20land%20use%20and%20land%20cover%20(LULC)%20within%20the%20lake%20between%201859%20and%202013%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20surrounding%20areas%20from%201962%20to%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.limno.2016.11.008%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20the%20demographic%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20the%20human%20population%20within%20the%20lake%20has%20surpassed%20double%20the%20national%20growth%20rate.%20These%20changes%20in%20both%20LULC%20and%20demographics%20have%20had%20adverse%20effects%20on%20the%20pollution%20status%20of%20the%20previously%20pristine%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Javed%20blames%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fwork-underway-in-srinagar-under-various-smart-city-projects-officials-123091200298_1.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20smart%20city%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20in%202019%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20influx%20of%20tourism%20which%20choked%20their%20spaces%20%E2%80%93%20the%20sewage%20has%20been%20polluting%20Dal%20for%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region%E2%80%99s%20accelerated%20development%20has%20led%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20fishing%20trade%20and%20displacement%20of%20people%20from%20their%20ancestral%20properties.%20This%20change%20is%20fuelled%20by%20the%20constant%20need%20for%20beautification%20of%20places%20like%20the%20Boulevard%20and%20the%20foreshore%20road-%20in%20which%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20the%20Hanji%20people%20simply%20do%20not%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20widening%20of%20the%20foreshore%20road%20along%20the%20Dal%2C%20under%20the%20Smart%20City%20Project%2C%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20members%20of%20Hanji%20community%20to%20put%20stalls%20of%20barbeque%20or%20selling%20of%20vegetables%20on%20roadside%20This%20has%20disrupted%20the%20livelihoods%20and%20ancestral%20fishing%20practices%20of%20many%20among%20the%20Hanji%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20filed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fenvironment-and-nature-india-lakes-kashmir-278cedc58a77adce627505452ca2f9a4%5C%22%3ETariq%20Ahmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20(a%20houseboat%20owner)%20in%202017%2C%20%E2%80%9CForty-four%20million%20litres%20(11%20million%20gallons)%20of%20sewage%20was%20released%20into%20the%20lake%20from%20the%20city%20each%20day.%20In%20addition%2C%20about%201%20million%20litres%20(260%2C000%20gallons)%20of%20sewage%20came%20from%20houseboats.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dominant%20narrative%20has%20been%20that%20the%20houseboats%20pollute%20the%20Dal%2C%20however%2C%20the%20findings%20showcase%20otherwise.%20The%20photographs%20taken%20by%20environmentalists%20and%20journalists%20highlight%20the%20extent%20of%20eutrophication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01141509%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-2.14.23-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22843%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01141509%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-2.14.23-PM.png%20843w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01141509%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-2.14.23-PM-300x215.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699604%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22604%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Land%20use%20land%20cover%20within%20the%20Dal%20lake%20from%201859%20to%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20condition%20of%20the%20Dal%20is%20the%20result%20of%20a%20complex%20mesh%20of%20activities%20happening%20throughout%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20as%20the%20surge%20of%20residents%20and%20tourists%20has%20grown%20exponentially.%20The%20findings%20from%20the%20interviews%20of%20Hanji%20people%20are%20in%20congruence%20with%20what%20the%20research%20and%20the%20local%20reporting%20have%20been%20suggesting%20that%20sewage%20dumping%2C%20population%20rise%20and%20mismanagement%20is%20causing%20irreversible%20damage%20to%20the%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20beautification%20of%20Dal%20is%20thriving%20%E2%80%93%20with%20proper%20roads%2C%20footpaths%2C%20and%20new%20shops%20opening%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20growing%20population%20of%20tourists%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lake%20itself%20is%20slowly%20dying%2C%20and%20with%20that%2C%20the%20Hanji%20community%20is%20also%20slowly%20being%20removed%20from%20their%20ancestral%20fishing%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoss%20of%20biodiversity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMapping%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20pollution%20happening%20at%20Dal%20is%20a%20mammoth%20effort%20which%20scientists%20have%20been%20carrying%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Hanji%20people%20have%20been%20experiencing%20these%20impacts%20even%20before%20the%20issue%20became%20mainstream.%20Fishermen%20who%20have%20been%20living%20inside%20the%20Dal%20for%20decades%20have%20mentioned%20how%20the%20fish%20count%20in%20Dal%20has%20gone%20down%20exponentially%2C%20and%20the%20native%20species%20have%20almost%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FlhcIWXttOO8%3Fsi%3DjLDBCKZmyOdO2GE1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20old%20fisherman%20who%20has%20been%20living%20in%20the%20Dal%20for%20decades%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20fish%20in%20the%20Dal%20are%20small.%20Because%20of%20the%20sewage%2C%20the%20fish%20have%20declined.%20This%20sewage%20affects%20the%20seeds%20of%20the%20fish.%20We%20used%20to%20cultivate%20lotus%20stem%20(Nadru)%20but%20that%20is%20also%20declining%20now%20%5BThe%20LCMA%20is%20using%20machines%20to%20clear%20the%20nadru%20growth%20in%20the%20Dal%5D.%20The%20floods%20had%20a%20devastating%20effect%20on%20the%20fish.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAzmat%2C%20another%20fisherman%20working%20in%20the%20Tailbal%20region%20of%20the%20lake%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20fish%20here%20used%20to%20be%20plenty%2C%20but%20now%20they%E2%80%99ve%20depleted%20significantly.%20We%20are%20left%20with%20little%20to%20no%20work.%20We%20face%20a%20lot%20of%20hardships%20because%20of%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20people%20used%20to%20rely%20on%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20which%20included%20various%20flora%20and%20fauna%2C%20which%20were%20also%20part%20of%20their%20diet.%20The%20eutrophication%20of%20the%20lake%20paired%20with%20reduced%20water%20quality%20has%20made%20the%20water%20unfit%20for%20anything%2C%20while%20the%20local%20authorities%20had%20installed%20Sewage%20Treatment%20Plants%20(STPs)%20to%20mitigate%20the%20inflow%20of%20toxic%20sewage%2C%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirobserver.net%2F2020%2F03%2F02%2F70-of-srinagars-sewerage-goes-into-dal-lake-experts%2F%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20their%20tragic%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20reported%20that%20about%2070%25%20of%20the%20sewage%20generated%20in%20Srinagar%20City%20finds%20its%20way%20into%20the%20Lake.%20Three%20STPs%20are%20functioning%20under%20the%20control%20of%20LAWDA.%20These%20are%20heavily%20over-utilised%20and%20under-maintained%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greaterkashmir.com%2Fkashmir%2Ftechnical-expert-committee-to-determine-buffers-around-dal-allied-water-bodies%2F%5C%22%3Ecommittee%20of%20experts%20(CoE)%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%20appointed%20by%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20according%20to%20GNS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20STPs%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20renovated%20soon%2C%20however%2C%20the%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirobserver.net%2F2023%2F10%2F03%2Fdal-lake-loses-sheen-to-red-algae-bloom%2F%5C%22%3ERed%20Algae%20bloom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dubbed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20phenomenon%E2%80%9D%20by%20government%20officials%2C%20seems%20to%20show%20no%20sign%20of%20change%20after%20two%20years%20of%20said%20%E2%80%98renovation%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20carried%20by%20a%20daily%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greaterkashmir.com%2Ftodays-paper%2Fsrinagar-city%2Frs-239-crore-spent-on-dal-lake-conservation-in-last-5-yrs-goi%2F%5C%22%3EGreater%20Kashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20March%2C%202023%2C%20the%20government%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20spent%20Rs%20759%20crore%20for%20cleaning%20of%20the%20Dal%20from%202002%20to%202018%20and%20the%20UT%20administration%20has%20spent%20Rs%20239%20crores%20from%202019-2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20spending%20so%20much%20on%20the%20cleaning%20of%20the%20Dal%2C%20the%20Hanjis%20do%20not%20see%20themselves%20as%20the%20part%20of%20the%20process%20except%20that%20they%20are%20employed%20by%20the%20LCMA%20department%20occasionally%20to%20manually%20clean%20the%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20have%20been%20beneficial%20if%20the%20government%20would%20have%20taken%20into%20consideration%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20elder%20generation%20of%20the%20fishing%20community%20living%20in%20the%20Dal%20by%20involving%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20impacts%20of%20environmental%20degradation%20and%20urbanisation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disappearing%20flora%20and%20fauna%20do%20not%20just%20create%20shifts%20in%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20but%20they%20also%20impact%20those%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20the%20ecosystem%20itself%20for%20their%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20destruction%20of%20fish%20has%20been%20devastating%20for%20the%20Hanji%20people%20economically.%20It%20is%20impacting%20their%20business%20and%20leading%20many%20of%20them%20towards%20losses%20and%20throwing%20them%20deeper%20into%20poverty.%C2%A0Since%20the%20Hanji%20community%20is%20a%20fishing%20community%2C%20their%20main%20source%20of%20income%20is%20selling%20fish%20and%20vegetables%20which%20grow%20out%20of%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FxxYLkVUMJNk%3Fsi%3DAB-vh2NBzzW-PZxx%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20explained%20by%20Azmat%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20inflation%20has%20risen.%20Prices%20of%20commodities%20keep%20rising.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20earn%20that%20much.%20We%20have%20to%20buy%20fish%20from%20outside%2C%20and%20if%20it%20gets%20spoilt%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20on%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Azmat%20talks%20about%20here%20is%20a%20real%20problem%20which%20is%20becoming%20commonplace.%20The%20ecosystem%20of%20the%20lake%20is%20destroyed%2C%20wherein%20no%20cultivation%20of%20any%20flora%2C%20or%20no%20breeding%20of%20any%20fish%20through%20seeds%20is%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20pushing%20Hanji%20people%20to%20buy%20fish%20from%20fish%20farms%20and%20other%20states%20and%20sell%20it%20at%20a%20loss.%20This%20economic%20loss%20is%20putting%20immense%20pressure%20on%20their%20livelihoods%20and%20causing%20them%20to%20move%20away%20from%20the%20field%20of%20work%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20issues%20are%20also%20exacerbated%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20support%20from%20the%20local%20authorities%20and%20the%20government.%20While%20only%20one%20interviewee%20mentioned%20that%20businesses%20were%20hit%20post%20Article%20370%20implementation%2C%20the%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%20bodies%20was%20a%20recurring%20theme%20in%20the%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20possess%20a%20fear%20of%20officials%20and%20hence%20were%20paranoid%20of%20researchers%20asking%20any%20questions%2C%20including%20on%20their%20daily%20lives%20or%20livelihoods.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20police%20come%20and%20destroy%20our%20fishes%2C%20throw%20them%20in%20water.%20In%20Lal%20Chowk%2C%20police%20throw%20them%20in%20Jhelum%20and%20we%20face%20loses%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ghulam%20Nabi%2C%20a%2052-year-old%20fisherman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20issue%20which%20almost%20all%20the%20interviewees%20talked%20about%20was%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20proper%20market%20to%20sell%20their%20produce.%20Many%20of%20them%20sit%20on%20the%20foothpath%20near%20the%20road%20and%20sell%20fish%2C%20and%20they%E2%80%99re%20told%20to%20move%20frequently%20because%20they%20disturb%20the%20%E2%80%98aesthetic%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20newly%20constructed%20roads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJana%2C%20a%2060-year-old%20woman%20who%20sells%20fish%20near%20the%20Dargah%20Hazratbal%20said%20that%20she%20has%20to%20pay%20rent%20to%20sit%20on%20the%20road%20and%20set%20up%20her%20stall%2C%20and%20the%20biggest%20problem%20she%20faces%20is%20the%20constant%20relocation%20to%20new%20locations%20as%20she%20has%20to%20carry%20all%20her%20belongings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhulam%20Mohammad%2C%20who%20sells%20fish%20on%20the%20foreshore%20road%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20municipality%2C%20they%20take%20all%20our%20stuff.%20I%20have%20kept%20my%20shikara%20%5Bboat%5D%20here%2C%20I%20put%20all%20my%20stuff%20in%20that%20and%20leave.%20They%20even%20take%20tubs%20with%20fish%20in%20it.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20used%20to%20sell%20fish%20on%20the%20other%20side%20but%20after%20they%20made%20the%20pathway%20along%20the%20road%20they%20had%20to%20shift.%20Our%20trade%20is%20based%20on%20water%2C%20we%20had%20asked%20them%20to%20at%20least%20make%20a%20stairwell%20along%20the%20road%20so%20that%20we%20may%20get%20some%20water%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20subjugation%20from%20authorities%20puts%20immense%20pressure%20on%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Hanji%20community%20because%20most%20of%20them%20are%20struggling%20already%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20as%20the%20sales%20of%20fish%20are%20almost%20always%20in%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20seem%20to%20believe%20that%20removing%20Hanji%20people%20from%20the%20area%20and%20relocating%20them%20to%20a%20new%20location%20will%20somehow%20improve%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20lake%20itself%2C%20but%20even%20after%20multiple%20attempts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thekashmirmonitor.net%2Fsave-dal-lake-sdrf-lwda-launch-major-drive-to-restore-glory-of-world-famous-water-body%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20issue%20remains%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20the%20huge%20sums%20being%20spent%20on%20the%20Save%20Dal%20Project%2C%20clearly%2C%20there%20is%20a%20deeper%20issue%20that%20the%20authorities%20are%20failing%20to%20understand%2C%20and%20the%20findings%20showcase%20how%20they%20might%20have%20been%20pushing%20away%20the%20solution%20all%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERole%20of%20the%20Hanji%20people%20in%20maintaining%20the%20ecosystem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20wants%20to%20beautify%20the%20Dal%2C%20so%20they%20relocated%20us%20but%20they%20are%20not%20able%20to%20keep%20it%20clean.%20We%20used%20to%20keep%20it%20clean%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Azmat%2C%20who%20emphasises%20on%20the%20role%20of%20the%20community%20in%20maintaining%20the%20Dal%20as%20well%20as%20keeping%20it%20in%20an%20equilibrium.%20The%20overall%20process%20of%20urbanisation%20and%20removal%20of%20Hanji%20people%20has%20led%20to%20significant%20changes%20in%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20might%20be%20removing%20the%20Hanji%20people%20from%20the%20areas%20for%20%E2%80%98aesthetic%E2%80%99%20reasons%2C%20it%20is%20having%20a%20counter%20effect%20because%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20condition%20was%20also%20a%20result%20of%20the%20care%20and%20practice%20which%20went%20into%20maintaining%20such%20a%20fragile%20ecosystem.%20The%20Hanji%20people%20had%20been%20a%20big%20part%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20prevalent%20use%20of%20%3Cem%3Elamba%20zaal%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20longer%20nets%2C%20which%20kill%20the%20seed-laying%20fish%2C%20and%20stop%20the%20fishes%20from%20procreating.%20The%20Hanji%20people%20used%20the%20%3Cem%3Egoal%20zaal%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20the%20round%20net%2C%20which%20requires%20skill%20to%20use%3B%20the%20entry%20of%20non-Hanji%20fishermen%20and%20the%20use%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Elamba%20zaal%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20them%20has%20been%20reducing%20the%20fish%20count%20further%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20people%2C%20then%2C%20seem%20to%20be%20eager%20to%20help%20maintain%20the%20lake%20but%20have%20been%20denied%20any%20chance%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20person%20asserted%20that%20the%20trade%20would%20have%20been%20different%20had%20there%20been%20a%20Mahigir%20person%20(fisherman)%20in%20the%20fisheries%20department%2C%20he%20adds%2C%E2%80%9CA%20Mahigir%20knows%20these%20waters%20by%20heart.%20He%20knows%20how%20to%20keep%20this%20clean.%20How%20to%20catch%20fish.%20How%20to%20use%20the%20net.%20Thus%2C%20they%20would%20have%20prevented%20the%20illegal%20fishing%20activities%20in%20the%20lake.%20The%20net%20destroys%20the%20seed.%20It%20has%20been%20banned.%20The%20Mahigir%20has%20the%20know-how%20of%20the%20lake.%20At%20least%2C%20they%20would%20have%20provided%20the%20information%20to%20the%20concerned%20depts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20idea%20which%20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fao.org%2F3%2Fw2352e%2FW2352E06.htm%5C%22%3EParticipatory%20Rural%20Appraisal%20(PRA)%3C%2Fa%3E%20framework%20employed%20in%20environmental%20projects%2C%20wherein%20the%20rural%20population%20is%20involved%20in%20the%20various%20processes%20of%20the%20project%2C%20so%20as%20to%20ensure%20true%20value%20to%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20apparent%20lack%20of%20representation%20of%20Hanji%20people%20in%20the%20decision-making%20mechanism%20which%20leads%20to%20such%20watered-down%20efforts%20to%20help%20the%20community.%20The%20official%20engineer%20of%20the%20LCMA%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Dal%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20LCMA%20but%20unfortunately%20we%20have%20other%20departments%20interfering%20in%20our%20work.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20have%20been%20tasked%20to%20clean%20the%20Dal%2C%20now%20fisheries%20department%20has%20provided%20the%20license%20for%20cultivating%20%3Cem%3Enadru%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20we%20tried%20to%20remove%20that%20but%20due%20to%20media%20highlights%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t.%20All%20the%20departments%20do%20as%20they%20wish.%20That%20is%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20sorry%20state%20of%20the%20Dal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20clearly%20shows%20the%20lack%20of%20coherence%20and%20clarity%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20organising%20a%20systematic%20approach%20towards%20reformation%20of%20the%20Dal%2C%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20hearing%20the%20people.%20These%20internal%20inefficiencies%20make%20apparent%20the%20need%20of%20a%20PRA-like%20framework%2C%20wherein%20the%20grassroots%20governance%20model%20can%20create%20a%20better%20way%20of%20handling%20sensitive%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20physical%20and%20social%20erasure%20of%20identity%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20Hanji%20people%20have%20been%20removed%20from%20their%20homes%2C%20their%20ancestral%20livelihoods%20have%20been%20destroyed%2C%20and%20their%20trade%20has%20changed%20so%20drastically%20that%20not%20many%20of%20them%20would%20want%20their%20children%20to%20continue%20the%20trade.%20This%20kind%20of%20impact%20is%20not%20just%20the%20result%20of%20environmental%20issues%2C%20it%20is%20a%20result%20of%20a%20systemic%20subjugation%20of%20a%20particular%20community%20amid%20a%20blind%20race%20for%20development%20and%20growth%20to%20fulfil%20the%20needs%20of%20one%20section%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20community%20has%20already%20been%20relocated%20to%20different%20regions%20which%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20carry%20out%20their%20activities%20as%20usual.%20With%20this%20displacement%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20just%20losing%20money%2C%20but%20also%20a%20longstanding%20part%20of%20their%20identity%20and%20belongingness%2C%20which%20is%20fuelled%20by%20a%20misrepresentation%20of%20their%20role%20in%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20lake%20and%20its%20%E2%80%98pollution%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20development%20is%20tainted%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20marginalisation%2C%20there%20is%20a%20visible%20difference%20in%20the%20house%20of%20the%20Hanji%20%3Cem%3Emohalla%20%3C%2Fem%3E(locality)%C2%A0and%20non-Hanji%20%3Cem%3Emohalla%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20if%20one%20utilises%20a%20spatial%20lens%2C%20it%20becomes%20apparent%20how%20the%20spatiality%20of%20development%20plays%20a%20big%20part%20in%20erasing%20the%20identity%20of%20these%20communities%20which%20have%20been%20part%20of%20this%20space%20even%20longer%20than%20most%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20be%20understood%20that%20fishing%20is%20not%20only%20the%20livelihood%20of%20the%20Hanji%20community%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20part%20of%20their%20culture.%20So%2C%20the%20displacement%20of%20the%20members%20of%20this%20community%20means%20denial%20of%20cultural%20identity%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0The%20cultural%20ramifications%20of%20rapid%20urbanisation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20halcyon%20days%20of%20the%20Dal%20Lake%20are%20slowly%20losing%20their%20charm%2C%20as%20the%20lake%20and%20its%20ancestral%20custodians%20of%20the%20Hanji%20community%20grapple%20with%20the%20repercussions%20of%20climate%20change%20amidst%20rapid%20urbanisation.%20Scientific%20findings%20and%20local%20narratives%20uncover%20the%20complex%20web%20of%20forces%20which%20has%20caused%20the%20decline%20of%20this%20once-pristine%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20599px)%2085vw%2C%20599px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185556%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.55.05-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185556%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.55.05-PM.png%20599w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185556%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.55.05-PM-300x224.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699695%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22448%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWeeds%20and%20algae%20growth%20on%20the%20interiors%20of%20the%20Dal%20Lake.%C2%A0Photo%3A%20Najam%20Us%20Saqib%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20community%20and%20their%20traditional%20way%20of%20life%20are%20being%20impacted%20immensely%20as%20the%20unrelenting%20degradation%20of%20the%20lake%20continues%20despite%20the%20efforts%20by%20the%20state.%20The%20removal%20of%20the%20Hanji%20people%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20beautification%20efforts%20is%20shortsighted%20and%20overlooks%20their%20valuable%20traditional%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20erosion%20of%20their%20identity%20is%20a%20consequence%20which%20might%20be%20the%20most%20irreversible%20and%20tragic%20of%20all%20the%20losses.%20This%20process%20is%20emblematic%20of%20the%20larger%20problem%20we%20face%20when%20balancing%20rapid%20growth%20and%20change%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcknowledging%20the%20inherent%20link%20between%20the%20Hanji%20people%2C%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20and%20sustainable%20development%20is%20vital.%20It%20emphasises%20the%20importance%20of%20inclusivity%2C%20community%20engagement%2C%20and%20preserving%20cultural%20identities%20to%20secure%20a%20harmonious%20and%20resilient%20future%20for%20this%20jewel%20in%20the%20crown%20of%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAcknowledgment%20Note%3A%20The%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvisualstoryboardscnes.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EVisual%20Storyboard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.jgu.edu.in%2Fjslh%2Fresearch-centres%2Fcentre-for-new-economics-studies%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eteam%20of%20CNES%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Dr.%20Khalid%20Wasim%20Hassan%20for%20his%20guidance%20with%20the%20fieldwork%20of%20the%20study.%20We%20also%20thank%20Ms.%20Maria%20Shawl%2C%20Mr.%20Zahid%20Sultan%2C%20and%20Ms.%20Bismah%20Yousuf%20for%20their%20help%20during%20the%20field%20work.%20Video%20essays%20from%20this%20field%20story%20are%20accessible%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutube.com%2Fplaylist%3Flist%3DPL8RbNXSvnr8Swc2c8BsmjH16QMVL--Ja6%26si%3DuEA9tc-JQpZU-w0C%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Dean%2C%20Office%20of%20Interdisciplinary%20Studies%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.jgu.edu.in%2Fjslh%2Fresearch-centres%2Fcentre-for-new-economics-studies%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNES%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E)%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20with%20Saw%20Swee%20Hock%20Southeast%20Asia%20Centre%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science%20and%